  "prompt": "What is meaning of \u0e2b\u0e25\u0e07\u0e01\u0e25\u0e34\u0e48\u0e19\u0e08\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e23\u0e4c?",
  "response": "\"\u0e2b\u0e25\u0e07\u0e01\u0e25\u0e34\u0e48\u0e19\u0e08\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e23\u0e4c\" (Long glin jan) is a Thai poetic expression that literally translates to \"lost in the scent of the moon.\" \n\nIn a metaphorical sense, this phrase typically means:\n- Being enchanted or mesmerized\n- Falling into a dreamy or romantic state\n- Being captivated by something beautiful or mysterious\n- Experiencing a sense of longing or nostalgia\n\nIt's often used in literature and poetry to describe a romantic or dreamy emotional state, where someone is deeply moved or lost in thought by something ethereal or intangible, much like being captivated by the subtle, unreachable essence of moonlight.",
